On Sat, 6 Aug 2005 16:03:55 -0700
In <7B0AADBE-23D8-4C63-ABE7-75360C874E13@lrde.epita.fr>
Qu=F4c Peyrot <chojin@lrde.epita.fr> wrote:
> Is there any existing camlp4 extensions to define a $ haskell-like =20
> operator?

Maybe "@" and "^" are right-associated.

# let ( ^$ ) f x =3D f x;;
val ( ^$ ) : ('a -> 'b) -> 'a -> 'b =3D <fun>
# print_string ^$ List.fold_left (fun x sum -> sum ^ x) "" ^$ ["1";"2";"3"]=
;;
321- : unit =3D ()

# let ( @$ )  f x =3D f x;;
val ( @$ ) : ('a -> 'b) -> 'a -> 'b =3D <fun>
#  print_string @$ List.fold_left (fun x sum -> sum ^ x) "" @$ ["1";"2";"3"=
];;
321- : unit =3D ()

